  "rationale": "<p>Choice C is correct. A linear function has a constant rate of change. From (1, 5) to (2, 8), <em>f</em> increases by 3 for an increase of 1 in <em>x</em>. Thus <em>f</em>(3) = 8 + 3 = 11.</p><p>Choices A, B, and D are incorrect and may result from miscomputing the rate of change.</p>",
